{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-page-js","path":"/blog/day-of-archaeology-2011/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 320px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/a55d4/day-of-archaeology.webp 320w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/b4845/day-of-archaeology.jpg 320w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/b4845/day-of-archaeology.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Day of Archaeology screenshot\"\n            title=\"Day of Archaeology screenshot\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Day of Archaeology screenshot</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>One of the projects that I'm working on, alongside some other digital archaeologists (Lorna Richardson, Matthew Law,\nJess Ogden, Stu Eve, Andrew Dufton and Tom Goskar) is the “The Day of Archaeology 2011”, a social media\nbased project that will allow archaeologists working all over the world to document what they do on one day, July\n29<sup>th</sup> 2011. I'm providing server space via the Portable Antiquities Scheme's underused backup box and also\nconfigured the WordPress install and open source twapperkeeper for storing the social buzz.</p>\n<p>This date coincides with the\n“<a href=\"http://festival.britarch.ac.uk/\" title=\"CBA festival website\">Festival of British Archaeology</a>“, which runs from\n16<sup>th</sup> – 31<sup>st</sup> July 2011 and is one of the hundreds of events being held to celebrate\narchaeology in the UK and beyond.</p>\n<p>So how does it work? Well, archaeologists taking part in the project will document their day through photography, video,\nfacebook activity, Twitter commentary and written blog posts. These will then be collated in realtime on the project's\ndedicated website <a href=\"http://dayofarchaeology.com\">The day of archaeology website</a>, which\nwill then provide a glimpse into a day in the life of people working in archaeology, from archaeological excavations to\nlaboratories, universities, community archaeology groups, education services, museums and offices. This project is open\nto everyone working or volunteering in any aspect of archaeology from anywhere in the world – and even those who\nhave defected! Currently, over 150 people and organisations have signed up. You could be next, so give archaeology a\nvoice!</p>\n<p>This innovative idea, follows on from the very successful “Day of Digital Humanities” and was dreamt up by\nMatthew Law and Lorna Richardson and was then built upon following a Twitter conversation and subs</p>\n<p>The project is supported by:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Portable Antiquities Scheme (providing server space for free)</li>\n<li>Council for British Archaeolog</li>\n<li>L-P Archaeology</li>\n<li>Wessex Archaeology</li>\n<li>UCL's Centre for Digital Humanities</li>\n<li>The Institute of Archaeology</li>\n<li>CASPAR</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The hashtag for this project is <a href=\"http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23dayofarch\">#dayofarch</a> and can be used\non tweets, blog posts and flickr photos to aggregate externally. Please consider using this tag if you refer to this\nproject.</p>","id":"092f1714-6aab-5bc6-b79c-f3f39543d017","timeToRead":1,"wordCount":{"words":339},"frontmatter":{"slug":"/blog/day-of-archaeology-2011/","date":"April 28, 2011","title":"Day of archaeology 2011","description":"A post about the day of archaeology","section":"blog","tags":["archaeology","public archaeology","museums","blogging","digital humanities"],"geo_lat":null,"geo_lon":null,"featuredImg":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/b5b43/day-of-archaeology.jpg","srcSet":"/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/ca5a2/day-of-archaeology.jpg 80w,\n/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/c16af/day-of-archaeology.jpg 160w,\n/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/b5b43/day-of-archaeology.jpg 320w","sizes":"(min-width: 320px) 320px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/abd73/day-of-archaeology.webp 80w,\n/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/70041/day-of-archaeology.webp 160w,\n/static/67288bdc1de55463cbca9cafafb2b48b/b5c5b/day-of-archaeology.webp 320w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 320px) 320px, 100vw"}]},"width":600,"height":600}}},"background":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/0360990bd214cf42ab30bb8c9aea9238/1b6fe/british-museum.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0360990bd214cf42ab30bb8c9aea9238/6c9bb/british-museum.jpg 256w,\n/static/0360990bd214cf42ab30bb8c9aea9238/c5fd3/british-museum.jpg 512w,\n/static/0360990bd214cf42ab30bb8c9aea9238/1b6fe/british-museum.jpg 1024w","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/0360990bd214cf42ab30bb8c9aea9238/f1118/british-museum.webp 256